A '''[[reward casket]] (medium)''' is received after completing the final clue of a [[Clue scroll (medium)|medium clue scroll]] trail, and contains the final reward for the trail.

While players can only have one of each type of clue scroll in their possession, they can possess unlimited amounts of reward caskets, and are eligible to receive clue scrolls again once it is obtained.

==Rewards==
Medium clues generate a minimum of 3 rewards and a maximum of 5, granting an average of 4 rewards per casket. The rewards consist of generic items, shared treasure trail items and items that are unique for medium clues. Additionally, players have a 1/30 chance to receive a [[master clue scroll]] upon opening a medium casket.

All droprates are confirmed by Mod Tide.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Tide|url=https://twitter.com/JagexTide/status/1131933683714330624|date=24 May 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.fo/WUqwD|archivedate=24 May 2019|quote=I know its been a while since the clue expansion but here is the information on clue scroll drop rates and loot chances! If anything changes I will keep you posted.|name=Clue rates tweet}}{{CiteGeneral|url=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/16pVNHdZyynmxIbM9mynRDYT0LQsWxq-vbDs4_7DpnGM/edit?usp=sharing|title=Clue scrolls 2019|author=|time=24 May 2019}} The listed rarities are per roll.

The average loot roll is worth {{Coins|floor({{Average drop value|raw=y}})}}, for an average value per casket of {{Coins|floor(4 * {{Average drop value|raw=y}})}}. The 1/30 chance of receiving a master clue scroll adds another {{Coins|floor(1/30 * 6 * {{MasterClueValue}})}}, for a total expected value per clue of {{Coins|floor(4 * {{MediumClueValue}} + 1/30 * 6 * {{MasterClueValue}})}}.

However, these averages are heavily skewed by the extremely high value of [[ranger boots]] compared to the rest of possible rewards. When they are removed from consideration, the average loot roll drops to {{Coins|floor({{Average_drop_value|raw=y}} - ({{GEP|Ranger boots}} * 1/11 * 1/103))}}, and the average medium clue drops to {{Coins|floor(4 * ({{Average_drop_value|raw=y}} - ({{GEP|Ranger boots}} * 1/11 * 1/103)))}}.

