==Trivia==
*[[Yew comp bow]]s used to be as common a reward as [[yew shortbow]]s, while players were not able to receive [[yew longbows]] as a reward at all. However after a [[Update:Barbarian Assault Ranged Rework|game update]] on [[25 January]] [[2018]], players started reporting yew longbows as a new common reward from their medium clue scrolls. Since then, yew comp bows also seem to be rarer to get as a reward. No changes to the Treasure Trails rewards table were mentioned in the official update post.
*Along with the [[Update:Treasure Trail Expansion (2016)|Treasure Trail expansion]] on [[6 July]] [[2016]], the Ancient, Armadyl and Bandos [[Vestment robes|vestment sets]] were completed with mitres, cloaks, stoles and croziers. These items were added as a reward for medium clue scrolls, even though Saradomin, Zamorak and Guthix stoles and croziers are rewards of hard clue scrolls.
*With the [[Update:Treasure Trail Expansion|Treasure Trail expansion]] on [[12 June]] [[2014]] update, 43 new unique rewards were added to medium clue scrolls. Two weeks later, [[Holy sandals]] were added in a [[26 June]] [[2014]] [[Update:Midsummer Event|update]]. The [[Update:Treasure Trail Expansion (2016)|Treasure Trail expansion]] on [[6 July]] [[2016]] added another 12 unique rewards to medium clue scrolls.
*Mod Mat K revealed in a 2016 data stream{{CiteVideo|title=Old School RuneScape Data Session with Mod Mat K!|author=Old School RuneScape
|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-5hXaHEzIM&t=465s|site=YouTube|timestamp=7:45}} that on average 7,000 medium clue scrolls were completed every day.

